An elderly man was killed in a fire which razed a Westville house on Monday afternoon. Rescue Care spokesman Garrith Jamieson said that medics had rushed to reports of the house fire in Serpentine Drive in Westville North. “Paramedics arrived at the scene to find the house was well alight with flames moving through a large portion of the structure‚” he said. “Sadly a man believed to be in his seventies sustained severe burns in the fire and passed away. There was nothing that paramedics were able to do for him and he was declared dead at the scene.” Jamieson said that no other injuries were reported and the police and eThekwini Metro fire department would investigate the cause.